{% extends 'check.j2' %}

{% block scope %}
- `{{ vars.skill_dir }}/SKILL.md` — verify it does NOT contain
  procedure / API / invocation sections.
- All `{{ vars.skill_dir }}/references/*.md` files (if any).
{% endblock %}

{% block rules %}
Read the reference conventions at `{{ vars.reference_path }}`.

This skill is `type: reference`. References are passive rule
sets — they should not contain workflow steps, API tables, or
commands.

Verify:

- Each `references/*.md` file covers exactly one topic. If a
  file mixes two unrelated topic groups, flag it for splitting.
- Files over 100 lines have a table of contents within the
  first 30 lines.
- Files over 300 lines warrant splitting (warning).
- Every `references/*.md` is reachable from SKILL.md via the
  markdown link graph (chains allowed).
- No `## Steps`, `## API`, `## Commands`, `## Invocation`, or
  `## Workflow` sections appear in SKILL.md.

Findings should target structure and reachability, not
formatting.
{% endblock %}
